                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Ben Schreck",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "I fixed it by making HADOOP_HOME=/usr in the worker environment. Pyarrow for some reason sets the hadoop executable to $HADOOP_HOME/bin/hadoop on python/pyarrow/hdfs.py:L137. $HADOOP_HOME on my system was already /usr/bin/hadoop, so this resulted in /usr/bin/hadoop/bin/hadoop, which resulted in a wrong $CLASSPATH.",
